@quartinochicago is one of river north‚Äôs best kept secrets when it comes to old school italian energy / bustling ambience / food / drinks / staff / $$ (I truly do not understand what witchcraft was performed to have such reasonable prices with the quality of food - blessed). It is quite nearly impossible not to have an amazing time here and it‚Äôs perfect for any number of people from solo dining at the bar to huge groups. Shout out to the quartino GOATS Reuben x2, best servers ever, only the real ones know. 

Order for a party of 3-4: (not pictured, but one of my fav eggplant parms in the city and it comes in a cute personal cast iron skillet a MUST order) 

‚Ä¢ gnocchi - extremely solid gnocchi rendition with fresh ricotta and basil and the sauce is as classic Italian as it gets. Def a staple in the order rotation 
‚Ä¢ penne alla vodka - in a civil union with vodka pasta for the rest of life, have never been in a more reliable relationship. this shit never misses. not my favorite rendition in chi, but is never a bad idea to throw in 
‚Ä¢ campania pizza - this is def the best pizza on the menu. if you are still ordering margherita pizza when miss omicron is testing all of our lives, you are simply not living.
‚Ä¢ crisp calamari - I can never not order calamari when it‚Äôs on the menu bc is there truly anything better than fried seafood + sauces on deck?? that being said, unfortunately this rendition does not make it into the chi calamari starting 5 roster :/ 

Anyways. Get your asses to quartino and make sure to order a espresso tini + lemon drop shot + carafes of red wine upon entry to ensure that vibes are on point

Did a very Chicago thing for the first time today. Neighboring hot dog stands Jim's Original and Express Grill on Union Street (near the former location of Maxwell Street Market) both claim to have invented the iconic Maxwell Street Polish in the late 1930s. Identical menues and prices. One is open 24 hours and the other closes at 1am. Neither joint seems to acknowledge the other's existence. 10/10 would do again.
